20. Final Interview Summary

If you remember only five things before an interview:

Every request starts with DNS, which converts a domain name into an IP address.
HTTP is stateless; sessions, cookies, or JWTs are used to maintain user state.
HTTPS uses TLS to encrypt communication between the client and server.
The request path is typically: Browser → DNS → TCP/TLS → Load Balancer → Server → Cache → Database → Response.
Performance is improved by caching, load balancing, and efficient network communication, not just faster code.
