3. What is TLS Session Resumption?

Normally

TLS handshake is expensive.

Session resumption lets client reuse previous cryptographic information, reducing handshake time and improving latency.

4. What is Head-of-Line Blocking?

If one packet is lost in TCP

All later packets wait.

Packet 1 ✔

Packet 2 Lost

Packet 3 Wait

Packet 4 Wait

HTTP/3 using QUIC reduces this issue.

